law.catch_line: Commonwealth seal, custody of -- Seal of Secretary of State.
law.text: The Secretary of State shall keep the seal of the Commonwealth, and a seal of office with the following device: The American eagle, in the center, surrounded by the words "Commonwealth of Kentucky, Office of the Secretary of State."
law.history: Recodified 1942 Ky. Acts ch. 208, sec. 1, effective October 1, 1942, from Ky. Stat. sec. 4537.
